#Gold
Ancient Egypt: Nubia
Roman Empire: Las Medulas, Dacia
Middle Ages: Mali/Ghana, Bambuk + Bure + Akan + Lobi fields
New World: Peru/Colombia, Brazil
Victorian Era: California, Victoria
20th century: South Africa

#Silver
Ancient Greece: Laurion (near Athens)
Roman Empire: Rio Tinto
Middle Ages: Kutná Hora (Czechia)
Renaissance: Jáchymov (Czechia)
New World: Potosí (Bolivia), Mexico

#Copper
Bronze Age: Cyprus
Ancient Egypt: Timna Valley (Israel)
Roman Empire: Rio Tinto
Renaissance: Falun (Sweden)
Victorian Era: Cornwall, Michigan
20th century: Chile

#Spices
Black pepper: Malabar coast, large volume
Cinnamon: Ceylon
Ginger: Malabar coast
Clove: Maluku Islands, high value
Nutmeg: Maluku Islands, high value
Cardamom: Malabar coast, high value

#Textiles
Calico: Malabar coast (southwest India), large volume
Chintz: Coromandel coast (southeast India)
Muslin: Bengal, high value
Silk: China, high value

#Incense
Frankincense: south Arabia, large volume
Myrrh: Horn of Africa, large volume
Agarwood: southeast Asia, high value

#Other
Porcelain: China
Indigo: India
Ivory: Swahili coast
